If you use an optional variable and don't sync data for that field for all users, any user who doesn't have that data populated shows as an error and won't sync successfully. > Add an SIS Variable
> This option allows you to select from the available fields that you are syncing to Clever. > Add Custom Text
> This option allows you to type out custom text that you would like to use in your formula. > Add a Function
> This option allows you to use functions to build a formula. For more context on how to use functions, review Common Operations . > Common operations
>  
> Clever Tip: Copy these formats from this article and directly paste them in the IDM setup for your email or password format. Then, click Add format to set the format (see image below). >  
>  
> - Description: Custom Format
> - First three letters of last name: {{substr name.last 0 3}}
> - Last two letters of student graduation year: {{substr student.graduation\_year -2 2}}
> - First name initial: {{substr name.first 0 1}}
> - Last 6 of SIS ID for student: {{substr student.sis\_id -6 6}}
> - Last 4 of SIS ID for teacher: {{substr student.sis\_id -4 4}}
> - First word of last name: {{textBefore name.last " "}}
> - Replace - with . in last name: {{replace name.last "-" "."}}
> - Date from student date of birth: {{formatDate student.dob "DD"}}
> - Initials of school name: {{initials school\_name}}
>  
