Follows the form: {{if <condition> <value if condition is true> <value if condition is false>}}
> - Formula: equals {{equals student.sis\_id “12345”}}; Example: For the sis\_id 12345, the formula results in “true”. For any other sis\_id, the formula results in “false”.; Description: Returns “true” when the two values equal each other, and “false” otherwise. > - Formula: not  {{not equals student.sis\_id “12345”}}; Example: For the sis\_id 12345, the formula results in “false”. For any other sis\_id, the formula results in “true”.; Description: Flips true values to false and false values to true. > - Formula: and  {{and equals student.sis\_id “12345” equals name.first “John”}}; Example: For sis\_id 12345 and name “John Doe”, the formula results in “true”.; Description: Returns true when both the first and second values are true. > - Formula: or   {{or equals student.sis\_id “12345” equals name.first “John”}}; Example: For sis\_id 12345 and the name “John Doe”, the formula results in true.; Description: Returns true when either the first or second values are true. Also returns true when both values are true. > - Formula: greater  {{greater student.graduation\_year “2034”}}; Example: For graduation\_year 2035 and above, this returns true. Otherwise, this returns false.; Description: Returns true when the first value is greater than the second value. > - Formula: less  {{less student.graduation\_year “2034”}}; Example: For graduation\_year 2033 and below, this returns true. Otherwise, this returns false.; Description: Returns true when the first value is less than the second value. > - Formula: contains
